ings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":69,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":78,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":89,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Anne Annesley was born in 1480, in Annesley, Nottinghamshire, England, her father, Ralph Annesley, was 27 and her mother, Lady Ralph Annesley, was 22. She married John Richard Perkins about 1533, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 2 November 1580, in Surrey, England, at the age of 100."},"et":{"1480–2 November 1580":"1480–2. november 1580","1480–1580":"1480–1580","1480–1541":"1480–1541","1513–1585":"1513–1585","1453–Male":"1453–Surnud","1458–Female":"1458–Surnud","10 January 1513":"10. jaanuar 1513","2 November 1580":"2. november 1580","1580":"1580","1480":"1480","15 March 1541":"15. märts 1541","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1458":"1458","1513":"1513","1453":"1453","1585":"1585","1541":"1541","abo